#. html
#: C:/Program
#: Files/Splunk/etc/apps/docusign_ta/default/data/ui/views/docusign_ta_overview.xml:5
msgid ""
"<h1>Protect your DocuSign eSignature deployment with DocuSign "
"Monitor</h1><p>As a DocuSign security or customer administrator for your "
"enterprise, you want to protect your eSignature\n"
"deployment from outside and inside threats.</p><p>You need timely "
"security notifications delivered directly to your existing security and "
"event management (SIEM)\n"
"system or visualization tool to take quick actions to mitigate threats "
"such as:\n"
"    <ul><li>External events</li><li>New previously unknown security "
"breach methods</li><li>Access from blocked IP addresses</li><li>Any "
"activity that causes your API usage to spike and/or drop</li><li>Third-"
"party integration breaches</li><li>Internal events</li><li>Fraudulent "
"behavior in legitimate accounts. For example, an employee who is leaving "
"the company may delete or download company "
"information.</li><li>Preventing signers from sharing document links, or "
"other ways putting envelope security at risk.</li><li>Risk-related errors"
" made by well-meaning users, such as too many login attempts or attempts "
"from one user to log into DocuSign from two locations.</li></ul>\n"
"</p><p>Monitor lets you actively track these types of incidents. It "
"provides alerts from potential malicious activities for your\n"
"DocuSign agreements and offers automatic recommendations to counteract "
"these threats.</p><h2>Splunk integration prerequisites for Monitor</h2>\n"
"Perform these prerequisite tasks before integrating Splunk with Monitor.\n"
"<ol><li>Make sure that your application has:\n"
"    <ul><li>An integration key</li><li>A defined redirect URL for your "
"integration key</li><li>An RSA key pair</li></ul>\n"
"</li><li>After completing the application prerequisites:\n"
"<ul><li>Request Application Consent as described in How to get an access "
"token with JWT Grant and Monitor API Authentication.</li><li>Create a JWT"
" Token.</li><li>Obtain the Access Token.</li></ul>\n"
"</li></ol>\n"
"<p><a href=\"https://developers.docusign.com/platform/auth/jwt/jwt-get-"
"token/\">How to get an access token with JWT Grant</a></p>\n"
"<p><a href=\"https://docs.docusign.com/supportdocs/pdf/docusign-"
"monitor.pdf#page=15&amp;zoom=100,0,0\">Monitor API Authentication</a></p>"
"\n"
"<p>\n"
"For Support contact: <a "
"href=\"mailto:dsmonitorfeedback@docusign.com\">dsmonitorfeedback@docusign.com</a>"
"\n"
"</p>"
msgstr ""

